gate: OPEN
v:4 role:qa x:mobile
task: S88 T6 — iOS device verification checklist
requires: [FRONTEND_DEV, QA]
sprint: S88

context: |
  Client issue is on a real older iPhone. Verify both paths: biometry
  convenience fixes AND trust-device direct entry with warning.

steps:
  1. Build iOS dev or release candidate from navitrack-mobile-apps.
  2. Biometry path: login → enable Face ID → kill app → Face ID unlock.
  3. Switch apps 2 min (< grace) → no prompt; 10 min (> grace) → Face ID.
  4. Cancel Face ID → login shows retry button, no password required.
  5. Trust device path: disable biometry → enable trust → confirm warning →
     kill app → reopen → main screen directly, no password.
  6. Trust device: explicit logout → password required.
  7. Record results in sprints/88/report.ti (pass/fail per scenario).

out:
  - sprints/88/report.ti

done:
  - All 6 scenarios pass on physical iOS device.
  - report.ti notes device model + iOS version.
  - Trust-device warning shown before enable (screenshot or step noted).
